<p>Russia carried out a wide overnight drone and missile assault across Ukraine on Wednesday, Oct. 22, 2025, killing at least six people, including children, and injuring dozens, Ukrainian officials said [apnews.com#1][theguardian.com#1][france24.com#1]. The strikes hit residential areas and deliberately targeted energy infrastructure, triggering emergency power blackouts across multiple regions as repair teams scrambled to restore service [apnews.com#1][euronews.com#2][aljazeera.com#1]. The wave of attacks came as diplomatic momentum stalled after plans for a Trump–Putin meeting were put on hold, raising fresh appeals from Kyiv for stronger international pressure and military support [theglobeandmail.com#1][apnews.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/gW_Q8Uv9_kZMjhZCt8ZyuvKylelcJdIilJGk8u0ZkIFTIM0kjePTAKIG8cMys0MQdiszIzg9SdvR3MGFWLHnq_8CfGjANssz2Ai-AVdqvRCdBDQvuqN30ejeAgeuTvfjjNvJwmQ77jDzpGP0E8JmPtoqg0K443tC8YSvX10npxdEQiENO2UKU2AEeYmZfE6-sGJiHSUlwVrCzc2n_8BDdySdMh6Ymn1r0wFeLXHOkefPdAN2rBmBh2Mnp7fD2zAfAiGcusm_LXr90mUWRA' alt='Residents clean the balcony of their flat in an apartment building damaged by a Russian drone strike in Zaporizhzhia, Ukraine, October 22, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Scale of assault: Some reports say the night-long barrage involved hundreds of drones plus dozens of missiles — descriptions include &#x27;over 400 drones and 28 missiles&#x27; — straining Ukraine&#x27;s defences [theguardian.com#1][ft.com#1].</li><li>Widespread targets: Authorities reported strikes or damage across at least ten regions and cities, including Kyiv, Odesa, Zaporizhzhia, Kharkiv and Dnipro, spreading impact well beyond a single front [apnews.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li><li>Children evacuated: A drone strike hit a private kindergarten in Kharkiv; officials said all 48 children were evacuated, one adult died and many children were treated for acute stress reactions [politico.eu#1][euronews.com#3].</li><li>Diplomatic fallout: President Trump put the planned meeting with President Putin on hold and said he did not want the summit to be &#x27;a waste of time,&#x27; a development that coincided with the renewed attacks [apnews.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Another night that proves Russia does not feel enough pressure for prolonging the war - Volodymyr Zelenskyy</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Ukraine (President Volodymyr Zelenskyy): Zelenskyy said the strikes show Russia &#x27;does not feel enough pressure&#x27; and urged the EU, United States and G7 to take steps to sanction Russia and increase support [apnews.com#1][theglobeandmail.com#1]. (<a href='https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-drones-war-putin-trump-2cf465171be371a29e24aa600293b691'>AP News</a>)</li><li>United States (White House / President Trump): The White House said there were no imminent plans for a Trump–Putin meeting after President Trump put the planned talks on hold, saying he did not want it to be &#x27;a waste of time&#x27; [straitstimes.com#1][apnews.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Russia-and-Ukraine-launch-overnight-missile-strikes-after-Trump-Putin-summit-delay'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Russia (official posture): Moscow rejected a proposed ceasefire and did not move forward with summit plans, and there was no immediate Russian defence ministry statement on some of the specific civilian-target reports such as the Kharkiv kindergarten strike [straitstimes.com#1][politico.eu#1]. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/russia-bomb-kindergarten-kharkiv-ukraine/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/russia-launches-deadly-wave-of-drone-missile-attacks-across-ukraine'>Russia launches deadly wave of drone, missile attacks across Ukraine</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/video/2025/10/22/russian-strikes-kill-six-in-massive-overnight-attack-on-ukraine'>Russian strikes kill six in m